text:
Washington Still Reels From the Quake of 2016 From the White House’s empty offices to overly giddy CPAC, everyone seems a little lost. By Feb. 23, 2017 7:15 p.m. ET 
Washington 
If Democrats have a brain in their head, they’ll let Supreme Court nominee Neil Gorsuch sail through the Senate. He’s too attractive. He has been frank and respectful in his meetings with them. He’s been candid about the man who nominated him, Donald Trump, to the reported irritation of the president. He is a thinker of clear conservative leanings who cannot be painted as radical because he’s radical as warm milk.
